# Annotation Guidelines v1.0

Goal:
Label short statements describing tiredness into one of three categories.

Labels:

F – Fatigue
- Explicit duration ≥ 2 weeks
- Persistent or daily tiredness
- Not clearly situational

S – Stress-related tiredness
- Clearly linked to work, exams, travel, sleep loss, or shifts
- Situational or temporary

U – Unclear
- Duration not specified
- Mixed or vague descriptions
- Requires inference

Rules:
- Use only information explicitly stated
- Do not infer duration or cause
- When in doubt, assign Unclear

